cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.DL, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new approach towards realizing declarative planning systems using answer set programming. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper discusses the transformation of the language κc to logic programs. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper introduces a new planning language κc. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is less likely but still possible as the paper reports experimental results on selected problems. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also less likely but possible as the paper discusses the potential of answer set planning as a valuable approach to expressive planning systems.
